cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.MM

This paper deals with the task of search and exploration in large networks of social multimedia users, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) due to the use of natural language processing techniques. The paper also involves the use of neural embeddings, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia data, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
